          <h2>Recent Tasting Note</h2>
        <div class="content"><div class="view view-tasting-note"><div class="view-content view-content-tasting-note"><div class="item-list"><ul><li><div class="view-item view-item-tasting-note"><div class="view-field view-data-node-body"><div class="field field-type-nodereference field-field-wine-tasted"><div class="field-label">Wine Tasted:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item odd"><a href="/web/20090919012556/http://www.intowine.com/wines/heartland-stickleback-red-2006">Heartland Stickleback Red 2006</a></div></div></div><div class="field field-type-text field-field-tasting-notes"><div class="field-label">Tasting Notes:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item odd">If ever there was a big ridge of tannins followed by a wash of broken-glass edged SUPER DUTY hotter than HADES (ᾍδης) PEPPER flavor to put me off on a wine, it was this Heartland Stickleback. A fiery blend of Holy moely Momma, Cabernet Sauvignon, Shiraz, Dolcetto and Grenache (what, to calm it down -nein, I think not). Hey, is the whole sun baked country a pizza oven? Is Fine for those  so inclined, or those among us permanently horizontal, but is way too big for former nut-ball gungho trained Ranger -whom it just doesn&#039;t suit? Will also kill grass in your sidewalk cracks, and keep moles out of your yard, no extra charge. </div></div></div><!-- google_ad_section_start --><!--paging_filter--><!-- google_ad_section_end --><div class="field field-type-number-integer field-field-wine-rating"><div class="field-label">Wine Rating:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item odd">80</div></div></div></div></div>
</li></ul></div></div><div class="view-footer view-footer-tasting-note"><!--paging_filter--><div class="more-link"><a href="/web/20090919012556/http://www.intowine.com/recent-tasting-notes">Read more...</a></div></div>
